```

But maybe this condition is missing in the implementation. Let me see what happens if lower > string length. In that case, `StringUtils.indexOf(str, " ", lower)` will likely return -1 (since we're looking for a space past the end of the string), and we'd still take substring(0, upper), which might be wrong.

